b'[<p><i><b>UFC Fight Night: Evans vs. Salmon</b></i> (also known as <i><b>UFC Fight Night 8</b></i>) was a <a href="/wiki/Mixed_martial_arts" title="Mixed martial arts">mixed martial arts</a> event held by the <a href="/wiki/Ultimate_Fighting_Championship" title="Ultimate Fighting Championship">Ultimate Fighting Championship</a> on  January 25, 2007 at the <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Seminole_Hard_Rock_Hotel_and_Casino_Hollywood" title="Seminole Hard Rock Hotel and Casino Hollywood">Seminole Hard Rock Hotel and Casino</a> in <a href="/wiki/Hollywood,_Florida" title="Hollywood, Florida">Hollywood, Florida</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-1"><a href="#cite_note-1">[1]</a></sup>  It was broadcast live in the <a href="/wiki/United_States" title="United States">United States</a> and <a href="/wiki/Canada" title="Canada">Canada</a> on <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Spike_TV" title="Spike TV">Spike TV</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-2"><a href="#cite_note-2">[2]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>This card featured the UFC debut of <a href="/wiki/Pride_Fighting_Championships" title="Pride Fighting Championships">PRIDE</a> and <a href="/wiki/Hero%27s" title="Hero\'s">Hero\'s</a> veteran <a href="/wiki/Heath_Herring" title="Heath Herring">Heath Herring</a>.  Originally scheduled for the main card was a bout between middleweight contestants <a href="/wiki/Nate_Marquardt" title="Nate Marquardt">Nate Marquardt</a> and <a href="/wiki/Dean_Lister" title="Dean Lister">Dean Lister</a>; it is believed that Spike TV influenced the eventual decision to remove the bout from the main card.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-3"><a href="#cite_note-3">[3]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>The following are the winner of the event\'s bonus awards given by the UFC.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-5"><a href="#cite_note-5">[4]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>The following figures are based on the fighter salary information that the UFC is required by law to submit to the state athletic commissions, including the winners\' bonuses.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-6"><a href="#cite_note-6">[5]</a></sup>\n</p>]'